{
	"name": "Edict of Silence",
	"type": "feature",
	"img": "icons/magic/fire/flame-burning-skull-orange.webp",
	"system": {
		"description": "<p>Your presence stifles rebellion. Your authority radiates like a commandment of flame. You gain proficiency in Intimidation, or if you are already proficient, an expertise die. When a creature within 60 feet casts a spell, you can use your reaction to brand their words with flame. The creature must make a Constitution Saving Throw (Spellcasting DC) or be silenced, making you unable to speak or cast spells with a vocalized component until the end of its next turn. If it was concentrating on a spell, it must immediately make a concentration check with disadvantage.</p>",
